   "source": [
    "# Topological Analysis of Heterogeneous Treatment Effects\n",
    "\n",
    "Companion notebook for the bachelor's thesis of **Apollonov N. A.** (HSE Faculty of Mathematics).\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook walks through the full pipeline:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Data.** Synthetic data from the heterogeneous PLM $Y = g_0(X) + A\\,\\tau_0(X) + U$, with a *known* CATE $\\tau_0$ whose superlevel-set topology is controlled by us.\n",
    "2. **Estimation.** Cross-fitted residualization $\\widetilde Y_i = Y_i - \\widehat m^{(-k(i))}(X_i),\\ \\widetilde A_i = A_i - \\widehat e^{(-k(i))}(X_i)$, then a regularised non-parametric second stage (R-learner-style) to obtain $\\widehat\\tau_n$.\n",
    "3. **Geometry.** Shape-regular triangulation $K_h$ of $\\Omega = [0,1]^2$ and PL interpolation $f_{n,h}$ of $\\widehat\\tau_n$ on the vertices of $K_h$.\n",
    "4. **Topology.** Persistent homology of the sublevel filtration of $-f_{n,h}$ (equivalently, the superlevel filtration of $f_{n,h}$) computed with `ripser`.\n",
    "5. **Landscape.** Persistence landscape $\\Lambda_0(f_{n,h})$ with discrete $L_p$ norms.\n",
    "6. **Empirical checks.** Stability $\\|\\Lambda_0(f) - \\Lambda_0(g)\\|_p \\le C_p\\,\\|f-g\\|_\\infty$ and convergence $\\|\\Lambda_0(f_{n,h}) - \\Lambda_0(\\tau_0)\\|_p = O_P(r_n + h^\\alpha)$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "6140d60b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys, os\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, os.path.abspath('..'))\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from src import data, cate, triangulation, topology, landscape, plotting\n",
    "\n",
    "np.set_printoptions(precision=4, suppress=True)\n",
    "%matplotlib inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5e9625e4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Data generation\n",
    "\n",
    "We use the custom topology-controlled DGP. The ground-truth $\\tau_0$ is a sum of two Gaussian bumps -- so $\\beta_0(A_t(\\tau_0)) = 2$ for thresholds $t$ in a non-trivial range, which is the topological feature we want to recover.\n",
    "\n",
    "A wrapper around `doubleml.datasets.make_plr_CCDDHNR2018` is also available (`data.make_doubleml_data`), but produces a *constant* CATE."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "80c1b905",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "n = 4000   d = 2   treated fraction = 0.515\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1100x400 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ds = data.make_topology_dgp(n=4000, topology='two_blobs', noise_sd=0.05, seed=0)\n",
    "print('n =', ds.n, '  d =', ds.d, '  treated fraction =', ds.A.mean().round(3))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(11, 4))\n",
    "plotting.plot_function_2d(ds.tau0, title=r'Ground-truth $\\tau_0$', ax=axes[0])\n",
    "axes[1].scatter(ds.X[ds.A == 0, 0], ds.X[ds.A == 0, 1], s=4, alpha=0.4, label='control')\n",
    "axes[1].scatter(ds.X[ds.A == 1, 0], ds.X[ds.A == 1, 1], s=4, alpha=0.4, label='treated')\n",
    "axes[1].set_aspect('equal'); axes[1].legend(); axes[1].set_title('observed covariates by treatment')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()"
   ]
  },
