   "source": [
    "## 7. Geometric (triangulation) error $h^\\alpha$\n",
    "\n",
    "Vary the mesh size $h$ for the *exact* function $\\tau_0$ (no statistical error) and check both\n",
    "\n",
    "* $\\|\\tau_{0,h} - \\tau_0\\|_\\infty \\lesssim h^\\alpha$ (here $\\alpha = 2$ because $\\tau_0 \\in C^\\infty$ and we use $P_1$ on a shape-regular family),\n",
    "* $\\|\\Lambda_0(\\tau_{0,h}) - \\Lambda_0(\\tau_0)\\|_p \\lesssim h^\\alpha$.\n",
    "\n",
    "We treat the finest mesh as a stand-in for the limit $h\\downarrow 0$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "2aa2a93b",
